  "text": "There is a complex system of cross-regulation that exists between bone and most other organs [CITATION_1] . Our studies provide further evidence that there are instances of shared molecular machinery for the production of acid in the stomach and in osteoclasts. TreeFam, a database of phylogenetic trees from animal genomes that can be used to infer the evolutionary history of genes, shows that Snx10 appears first in Osteichthyes, the bony fishes (http://www.treefam.org/ family/TF332117). The acid-secreting stomach also evolved in bony fishes. This raises the intriguing prospect that the osteoclastic and gastric acid producing systems evolved simultaneously during vertebrate evolution, together with emergence of a mineralized skeleton, utilizing some of the same genes.",
